    Time: 
</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH="517"><FONT SIZE="2">
    Friday 27th April 2001, 5:00 pm  EDT
</FONT>
</TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="96"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#CA0202">
    Levels: 
</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH="517"><FONT SIZE="2">
    1 to 1
</FONT>
</TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#E8E2E2"><TD VALIGN="top" WIDTH="96"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#CA0202">
    Details: 
</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH="517"><FONT SIZE="2">
    This is a fun event rather than something to camp for items or experience.  
    <p>
    There will be an entry fee amounting to your level equivalent of PP and prizes will be awarded for the first 3 teams to reach the finish line.
    <p>
    <b>Rules:</b><br>
    Every participant will create a level 1 troll called "Troll<charname>"  e.g. Trollfoxxs, Trollcallandria, Trollsoulsnatcher.  If your resulting name is too long, then call yourself Trollsomething where we can identify you easily as to who your main character is.  
    <p>
    Trolls can be of any class but MUST be level 1 at the start of the event.
    <p>
    Trolls will be partnered up into teams of 2.  If there are a large turnout then I may allocate trolls into teams of 3 or more.
    <P>
    For the race only, Trolls will be guilded so you can announce your progress / gloat / taunt your competitors.  You must /guildremove after the event.  Announcing your arrival in the next zone via /gu is always a good way of taunting people.
    <p>
    You may not be buffed with anything you cannot cast yourselves except when given a buff by a race 'steward'.  The only exception is shaman trolls who can buff their team mates.  If anyone casts sow on you then you must cancel it.  If you are caught buffed then you will be asked to suicide and return to your bind point.  Certain stages of the race have different buff rules but the no buffing rule applies normally.  No teleports or other movement spells.
    <p>
    You may interfere / train / ks and generally hamper any other troll in the race by fair means or foul, in fact I encourage you to :)
    <p>
    A steward will give you an item at each stage.  If you dont have all the items when you get to the finish, then you will be disqualified.
    <p>
    <b>Stage 1: Innothule Swamp to East Freeport</b><br>
    Trolls will race from Innothule to East FP.  Each troll will be given 5 alcoholic drinks which they must consume before setting forth.  All members of the winning team must reach East FP and /hug the Steward and all must be present in East FP (so no hugging then getting killed).  You will be bound here for the second leg of the race but <b>only</b> if you are still level 1.
    <p>
    <b>Stage 2: East Freeport to Temple of Solusek Ro</b><br>
    You must run from East Freeport to the Temple of Solusek Ro, which is in Lavastorm Mountains.  This must be done via running to West Freeport first and drinking 5 drinks (obtain drinks off the steward).  You must also make level 2 while in West Freeport.  You are to announce a huge DING in /guildsay and then run off to the Temple of Sol Ro.  The final steward in Temple of Sol Ro will not be easy to find so you may have to hunt around. Once you have found the steward, give them a /bonk to recieve your stage 2 marker.
    <p>
    <b>Stage 3: Temple of Solusek Ro to The Arena</b><br>
    This is a no-holds-barred stage.  Practice your "Sow plz" and "HP buff plz" technique. (Teleports are still banned).  You still may not be buffed from anyone in the guild unless it is a steward.  To win, all members of your team must make it to the arena intact and hit the steward for at least one point of damage.  You will also be bound here.
    <p>
    <b>Stage 4: Hunt the Naked Officer !</b><br>
    Just for your pleasure, an officer will be stripped and thrown into the arena for you all to chase around and kill.  You can beg or borrow buffs from anyone else in the area to aid you.  The winning team will be the one who slays the offending official.  Did I mention that you must also be blind drunk when doing this?  /cackle
    <p>
    For stages 1-3 a bonus will be awarded for bringing the steward an item.  The item will be disclosed at the start of the stage.  Be warned though, you must still be level 1 before you complete stage 1.
    <P>
    Have fun!
</FONT>
